HEADWORD: Catching
<hw>Catch"ing</hw> <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Infectious;
contagious.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Captivating; alluring.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Catching</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Catching
<hw>Catch"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of seizing or taking hold
of.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Catching bargain</b></col> <fld>(Law)</fld>, <cd>a
bargain made with an heir expectant for the purchase of his expectancy
at an inadequate price.</cd> <rj><au>Bouvier.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Catch-meadow</ent>⟦br⟧
